data.chText: 不为别人着想的；不体谅别人的；考虑不周的
data.enText: not giving enough thought to other people's feelings or needs

data.chText: 你连个电话也不打，不够体谅人。
data.enText: It was inconsiderate of you not to call.

tr: lacking regard for the rights or feelings of others

example: prejudice is the holding of unconsidered opinions

value.def: If you accuse someone of being inconsiderate, you mean that they do not take enough care over how their words or actions will affect other people.

example.ex: Motorists were criticised for being inconsiderate to pedestrians.
example.tran: 开车的人因不考虑行人而受到指责。
他不替别人着想的行为

value.tran: 不体谅别人的;不替别人着想的
